URL reference: https://www.theregister.com/2025/01/24/kubernetes_windows_nodes_bug/
DateReviewed: 2025-02-18
Description: This article is about a Window Kubernetes exploit, and how to mitigate the impact. The flaw allows attackers to reach SYSTEM privs, basically the keys to the kingdom on Windows. It does require a few things to be in place - K8s older than 1.32.1, beta features enabled and configured to run Log Query. The issue is that through the API, an attacker can inject commands into a parameter called "pattern" which isn't validated properly. The people who discovered this issue don't think it is too widespread, due to the several conditions needed to be exploitable. But if you have the conditions, explotation is fairly easy.
BottomLine: Good discussion of a Windows Kubernetes security exploit and mitigations
